cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use Myco in research or a derived substrate, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "Myco — Agent-First Symbiotic Cognitive Substrate"
abstract: >-
  Myco is a long-lived, self-validating cognitive substrate designed exclusively
  for LLM agents. Eighteen manifest-driven verbs (germinate / hunger / eat /
  sense / forage / assimilate / digest / sporulate / traverse / propagate /
  immune / senesce / fruit / molt / winnow / ramify / graft / brief) compose the
  ingest → digest → circulate → self-check → evolve life cycle. Twenty-five
  lint dimensions enforce contract invariants (R1–R7) mechanically, including
  atomic-write R6 enforcement, LLM-provider boundary (MP1/MP2), and graph
  connectedness (SE1/SE3). The kernel itself is a substrate — editable by
  default — so the agent that maintains Myco is the same agent that uses it.
